#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
macOS TCP connection quality TUI.

This intentionally keeps OS-specific collection behind a provider boundary.
macOS does not expose Linux ss(8)-style per-socket RTT/cwnd/retrans details
through netstat(1), so this provider reports the kernel TCP PCB table fields
that are available: queues, states, byte counters, socket buffer watermarks,
process names, plus global TCP statistics when netstat -s is permitted.
"""

